                            <comment id="12481" author="ndeloof" created="Thu, 3 Mar 2005 01:52:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just a comment because I&apos;m not sure my description of the bug is really clear.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ReloadableResourceBundleMessageSource cannot be refreshed until cacheMillis &amp;lt; 0. See resolveCode &amp;amp; resolveCodeWithoutArguments, a merged properties cahce is used.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When enabling reaload (cacheMillis &amp;gt;= 0) ReloadableResourceBundleMessageSource cannot use any resource that isn&apos;t readable as a filesystem resource. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I suggest :&lt;br/&gt;
1. Allow clear/refresh on merged properties for programmatic hot-reload of resources.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. Allow use of non file-system resources mixed by simply not skipping loading a resource if getFile() throws an IOException.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12484" author="ndeloof" created="Thu, 3 Mar 2005 18:49:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch proposal to solve this issue :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;clear merged properties on clearCache()&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;load properties even if lastModified cannot be read.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12711" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Fri, 25 Mar 2005 02:36:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for spotting those! I&apos;ve fixed both issues.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
